This schema allow to perform system operations on the Domogik application
like start or stop a module.

DOMOGIK.SYSTEM Message Specification

    * Class = DOMOGIK
    * Type = SYSTEM

This schema provides basic information relating to <short description>

=== XPL-TRIG Structure ===
xpl.trig message should be sent as an acknowledgement to a xpl.cmnd command.

DOMOGIK.SYSTEM
{
COMMAND=command to send
MODULE=name of the module concerned by the command|*
[FORCE=0|1]
[ERROR=error message if error occurs, 255 char max]
}

=== XPL-CMND Structure ===

DOMOGIK.SYSTEM
{
COMMAND=command to send
MODULE=name of the module concerned by the command|*
[FORCE=0|1]
}

=== XPL-STAT Structure ===


HBEAT.*
{
(hbeat items)
}

Schema Specific Notes
COMMAND value can be one of :

* START : Start a component
* STOP : Stop a component
* PING : Ask all components to reply (MODULE should equals '*', FORCE isn't used)
* RELOAD : If the module is able to do, refresh its config and reload it.
* PUSH_CONFIG : Send all the config items on the network. Should be used to refresh the config in database side
